    Create DOCTYPE HTML structure.
    Import CSS from http://localhost:3000/static/style.css.
    Create a header titled Login Page.
    Create a body describing the page to the user.
    Tell users they can create accounts to manage their profiles and animals.
    Tell users they can login by entering their username and password.
    Add line breaks between descriptions and forms.
    Copyright: PawPair Team 2023.
-->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Login Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://localhost:3000/static/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Login Page</h1>
    <!--
        Create a navigation bar routing: Home (/) and Animals (/animals).
        Separate links with pipes.
    -->
    <div class="navbar">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        |
        <a href="/animals">Animals</a>
    </div>
    <p>
        Welcome to the PawPair login page! Here you can create an account to manage your profile and animals, or login to an existing account.
    </p>
    <p>
        To create an account, click the "Create Account" button below. To login to an existing account, enter your username and password below.
    </p>
    <br>
    <form action="http://localhost:3000/create_account">
        <input type="submit" value="Create Account">
    </form>
    <br>
    <form action="http://localhost:3000/login" method="post">
        <label for="username">Username:</label>
        <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required>
        <br>
        <label for="password">Password:</label>
        <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required>
        <br>
        <input type="submit" value="Login">
    </form>
    <br>
    <p>
        &copy; PawPair Team 2023
    </p>
</body>
</html>
